<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10110066>
    dc:description "Figs 1-11: Panscopaeus lithocharoides: habitus (1); forebody (2); median dorsal portion of head (3); labrum (4); anterior median portion of labrum (5); ligula (6); left and right mandible (7-8); median dorsal portion of pronotum (9); male sternite VIII (10-11). Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2: 0.5 mm; 10-11: 0.2 mm; 3-9: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10110066/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10110068>
    dc:description "Figs 12-21: Panscopaeus lithocharoides: aedeagus in lateral view of males from Japan (12-14), China (15), and Nepal (18); apical portion in lateral and in ventral view of holotype of M. deharvengi (16-17); aedeagus in ventral view of males from Nepal (19), Japan (20), and China (21). Scale bar: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10110068/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

